lio manager wealth manager david born cfa cfp® portfolio manager wealth manager david began his career in 007 in morgan stanley’s financial advisor training program moving to highmark capital management a subsidiary of union bank progressing from internal wholesaler of highmark mutual funds to assistant vice president and assistant portfolio manager  david earned his bachelor’s degree from the university of california berkeley with concentrations in finance and economics  after taking a sabbatical to pursue his dream of traveling the world david is happy to return to his roots in the bay area  in his free time david enjoys spending time with family and friends drinking a good coffee playing water polo and hiking with his dog dillon mcgill cfp® wealth manager dillon mcgill cfp® wealth manager dillon started his career in wealth management as a member of the operations group for an independent advisory firm his passion is listening to clients as they share their life experiences learning what they care about most so he can better help them achieve their goals as a wealth manager deeply committed to our investment process and the success of each and every one of our clients he is a great addition to the grubman team dillon earned a bachelor of science in kinesiology from california polytechnic state university san luis obispo and holds professional certificates in personal financial planning and accounting from the university of california santa barbara’s university extension he is a member of the financial planning association fpa and is the social media coordinator of the fpa nexgen national leadership team outside of work dillon enjoys spending time with his family and friends participating in action sports like motocross listening to music and taking photographs jill martin operations manager jill martin operations manager having worn many hats at grubman wealth management over the years jill now ensures the smooth operation of all processes and services delivery f